<page_title>Double-clicking a toolbar button to bring up a customization dialog window</page_title>
<text> Double-clicking a toolbar button to bring up a customization dialog window
You can always double-click a toolbar button to bring up a dialog window for customizing the corresponding action, if there is any. This functionality has been around for a long time but no one seems to have noticed it. For example, if you are to bring up the Lennard-Jones graph for adjusting the VDW parameters, you can double-click on one of the four buttons for inserting atoms, if you have either one of them on your toolbar. You need not go through the atom property edtor or the model property editor to get to the Lennard-Jones graph.
Double-click on the three pre-made molecules to bring up dialog box for customizing the bond length, the bond angle, and the bond strength, for the next molecule to be dropped into the box.
 </text>
